DUNGEON GRIND — IMPROVEMENT PROPOSALS
======================================
Updated: February 2026

Ranked suggestions for new features and systems, from most impactful to least.
Items marked [SELECTED] were chosen for implementation.
Items marked [DONE] have been implemented.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#1  Prestige / New Game+ System
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
After clearing Dungeon 9 boss, option to reset to Lv1 with a permanent
multiplier (+5% damage and XP per prestige level). Keeps loot, keeps
achievements. Adds infinite replayability to the endgame loop.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#2  Companion / Pet System
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Passive companion that provides a small bonus (e.g., +10% gold, +5% crit,
periodic heal). Earned from boss kills or achievements. One active at a time,
stored in a collection. Low-effort way to add collection depth.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#3  Dungeon Exploration with Rooms
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Instead of infinite enemy spawns, dungeons have 10-20 rooms. Each room has
a random encounter (enemy, treasure chest, trap, shrine buff). Boss is the
final room. Creates a sense of progression within each dungeon run.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#4  Crafting System
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Enemies drop materials (Leather, Iron, Gems). Combine materials to craft
items or upgrade existing ones. Adds an alternate progression path to pure
loot RNG. Recipes discovered in dungeons or from boss kills.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#5  Achievement System                                    [DONE]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Track milestones (first boss kill, 1000 kills, max level, full legendary
set). Achievements grant small permanent bonuses. Bitfield storage in Hero,
check hooks after kills/boss/level-ups/equipment changes. New encyclopedia
sub-screen to view progress.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#6  Dungeon Hard Mode with Affixes                        [DONE]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
After clearing a dungeon (beating boss), unlock hard mode with random affixes
(enemies +30% HP, hero -20% healing, bosses enrage after 60s). Better loot
as reward. Per-dungeon unlock flag in Hero, modifier applied in combat.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#7  Passive Skill Tree
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Separate from active skills. Spend "insight points" (earned every 5 levels)
on a branching tree of small passives: +3% crit, +5% gold, +10 HP, etc.
Adds build diversity without touching the active skill system.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#8  Combat Log DPS/HPS Tracking                           [DONE]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Track total damage dealt, taken, healed, and ticks elapsed during combat.
Display DPS/HPS in the combat log or enemy panel. Counters in GameState,
no save changes needed. Helps players evaluate builds quantitatively.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#9  Rare Elite Enemy Encounters                           [DONE]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
5% chance on spawn to create elite variant (golden name, 3x stats, guaranteed
rare+ drop). Flag in GameState, minor changes to combat_spawn. Adds exciting
moments to the grind loop.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#10  Cosmetic Title System                                [DONE]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Earn titles from achievements and boss kills. Stored in Hero, displayed in
header bar. Title selection UI. Pure cosmetic reward that signals progression.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#11  Equipment Menu Redesign                              [DONE]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Problems: names truncated to 15 chars, no way to browse by slot, no sorting,
cluttered bag display.

Solution:
  - Sort inventory by Rarity (desc), Slot, or Level (desc) — toggle with [S]
  - Filter by equipment slot using left/right keys — cycle All/Weapon/.../Amulet
  - Wider item names: 18 chars for equipped, 21-23 chars for bag items
  - 3-char slot abbreviations (Wpn, Hlm, Cht, Leg, Bts, Rng, Aml)
  - Single-char slot tag in bag "All" view (W, H, C, L, B, R, A)
  - Filter/sort bar between equipped section and bag
  - Sorted view is UI-only (uses index array, doesn't modify inventory order)
